title: Jazbaa First Day (Friday) Box Office Collections: Fails To Do Well
text:
Receive all updates via Facebook. Just Click the Like Button Below Don't ask Again 
Aishwarya Rai Bachchan 's Jazbaa has made some decent collections on the first day of its release. The film has not managed to break any records as of now, but it is doing decent business. Jazbaa was directed by Sanjay Gupta with a budget of Rs 32 crores and released in over 1800 screens. The film has received fairly good reviews, only finding few flaws of overacting. The film did well in the middle east region, Taran Adarsh reported, #Jazbaa embarks on a STRONG start in UAE and GCC. Collects AED 450,000 [₹ 79.32 lacs] on Thu."
WOW-Rajinikanth Shocked Onlookers By Touching Amitabh's Feet In India, the film has managed to just Rs 4.23 crores, Tran tweeted the collections, "#Jazbaa Fri ₹ 4.23 cr. India biz... Biz gathered momentum towards evening/night shows... Expect an upward trend on Sat."The business is expected to grow over 50% on Saturday. The collections may have been affected by the release of a top Telugu movie, Rudhramadevi which starred top actors like Allu Arjun, Anushka Shetty and Rana Daggubati. 
The competition in South India seems to have affected the collections but with good word of mouth promotions, the film may end up doing well and favour Jazbaa Box Office collections.
